Spring data JPA vs JPA vs Hibernate vs JDBC

 1.JDBC
JDBC need mapper to map fields with DB fields
we use actual sql query in code with same names which present in DB not in entity
It does not read @table @column due to it annotations consist in jpa package and jdbc not present or not accesible to that package
It not give data or map directly to our java entity , we need to set explicitly from resultset to entity because it return data in resultset.
It not Supports transaction management.

2.Hibernate
It is an ORM tool
ORM- Object Relational Mapping allows to map java object fields directly to DB columns
Hibernate is a implementation of JPA
The @Entity, @Table, @column annotation is from package jpa-jakarta.persistence and this annotations use by hibernate means hibernate is implementation of jpa
Hibernate code written/implement in jpa package
hibernate dependancy is present inside the jpa dependancy
we use hql queries like String query="from emloyeee where id=:id";
we use sessionfactory.openSession();   ||     query.setParameter();
we follow java entity field names in query
so why we need to modify and upgrade to jpa or spring data jpa:
reason: there are multiple orm tools like EclipseLink, MyBatis and they have different implementations so if we need to switch from one tool to another it is difficult

3.JPA
It is one step above to hibernate and other ORM tools. It defines a standard set of methods that are to be implemented by this ORM tools.
Spring boot consider the hibernate is default implementation of JPA.
hibernate implement JPA. and if we want to change from one ORM to another then just need to change implement.
EntityManager is an interface that can be consider as JPA.

4.Spring data JPA.   --JPARepository inteface
It is built on top of JPA. 
It is a module i.e it's a Spring boot project which has introduce even more boilerplate.
It remove bolier plate code that we need to write everty time.
EX:(Derived Queries) - Employee finByIdAndNameAndDepartment(Long id, String name, String department);

