PAGINATION, SORTING & FILTERING
===============================

1) PAGINATION
==============
- Used to fetch data page by page.
- Improves performance.
- Avoids loading huge records at once.

Example:
--------
Page 1 -> First 10 records
Page 2 -> Next 10 records


SPRING DATA JPA PAGINATION
==========================

Interfaces Used
---------------
- Pageable
- Page


Example
=======

@GetMapping("/users")
public Page<User> getUsers(Pageable pageable) {

    return userRepository.findAll(pageable);
}


URL Example
===========

/users?page=0&size=5

Meaning:
--------
page=0  -> First page
size=5  -> 5 records per page


PAGE METHODS
============

page.getContent()
-----------------
Returns records list.

page.getTotalElements()
-----------------------
Returns total records count.

page.getTotalPages()
-------------------
Returns total pages count.

page.getNumber()
----------------
Current page number.


2) SORTING
==========
- Used to arrange records.
- Ascending or Descending order.

Types:
------
ASC  -> Ascending
DESC -> Descending


SORT EXAMPLE
============

@GetMapping("/users")
public List<User> getUsers() {

    return userRepository.findAll(
        Sort.by(Sort.Direction.ASC, "name")
    );
}


